# Mentor (Socrates)

`MentorBubble.tsx` is the AI chat component. Completions depend on **`NessoSettings.aiMode`**:

- **`remote`** (default) — OpenAI-compatible **`POST …/chat/completions`** via `fetch`. Base URL, model, and optional API key come from `aiBaseUrl`, `aiModel`, `aiApiKey`; there is no environment-variable fallback for the key.
- **`local`** — In-browser **WebGPU** inference via `@mlc-ai/web-llm` in `src/llm/webllm.ts`. `App.tsx` runs `initWebLLM()` when `aiMode === 'local'` so the MLC engine starts loading without opening Settings first. `MentorBubble` subscribes with `useWebLLM()` (status, `progress`, `progressText`) for a loading bar, placeholder, and transcript message; chat input stays disabled until `status === 'ready'`. `getEngine()` exposes `MLCEngine` for `engine.chat.completions.create` with the same message shape as the remote path.

## Setup

Configure under **Settings** (gear, **⌘,**): **Appearance**, **AI**, **Review** (FSRS live in **Review** for the full-screen review overlay only).

## Persona

Socrates is a Socratic mentor: mostly questions, almost no lecturing. Rules live in `MENTOR_BASE` inside `MentorBubble.tsx`:

- No graph edits in dialogue (do not propose new nodes/edges or renames).
- Default one short question; explain only to frame it; aim under ~120 words (hard cap via `MENTOR_MAX_TOKENS`).
- No emojis or flattery; sparse `*asterisks*` on key terms; no JSON or pseudo-graph markup.

## System prompt (single chat)

There are **no mode tabs**. `buildGraphChatPrompt()` builds one system string: graph snapshot — up to `MAX_SNAPSHOT_NODES` nodes with stability labels (remainder summarized if larger), up to `MAX_SNAPSHOT_EDGES` edges (`2×` the node cap by default), optional selection (node or full edge path) — plus `MENTOR_BASE`. Each send recomputes the prompt from the live store so new edits appear on the next turn.

On panel open, graph switch, or local-model-ready transition, the first mentor line is fetched by POSTing a short synthetic user turn (“Hello — I want to discuss…”) with the current system prompt.

## Rendering

Assistant `Message` text is HTML via **`marked`** (`renderMarkdown()` in `MentorBubble`, sync mode). User-authored bubbles remain plain text in a `<span>`.

## Selection vs history

`history` remains local component state. Exploration chat uses `selectedNode` / `selectedEdge` only inside `buildGraphChatPrompt` on each message, not as a trigger for selection-driven seed messages.

## Panel open/closed

Whether the mentor **card** is expanded is `mentorPanelExpanded` on `useGraphStore`, updated via `setMentorPanelExpanded`. It is persisted with the rest of UI chrome (`zustand` `persist` → localStorage). The FAB remains visible when collapsed.

## Message history

`history: Message[]` is local to `MentorBubble` (not in the store). It resets when the panel opens again, the graph changes, or local engine readiness changes during the opening sequence. Do not persist chat history to the store.

## API call

**Remote:** `fetch(`${aiBaseUrl}/chat/completions`, …)` with JSON body:

- `model` — `settings.aiModel`
- `max_tokens` — `MENTOR_MAX_TOKENS` (`220`, aligned with ~120-word replies)
- `messages` — `[{ role: 'system', content: buildGraphChatPrompt() }, …]` plus full `history` turns mapped to `user` / `assistant` roles.

`Authorization: Bearer …` is sent when `settings.aiApiKey` is non-empty.

**Local:** After `initWebLLM()` completes, `getEngine()` from `webllm.ts` is non-null. Until then the UI blocks sends. Then `engine.chat.completions.create({ model: LOCAL_MODEL_ID, max_tokens: MENTOR_MAX_TOKENS, messages })` with the same `messages` array built for remote mode.
